FAQ:


&lt;b&gt;Can you create sub accounts for the control panel?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
No you cannot.

&lt;b&gt;How does your spam filtering work?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
I take the role of managing the spam filters. If you receive spam it should land in your Spam box. If it lands in your inbox, forward it to spam@mxroute.com for review.

&lt;b&gt;Can I upgrade anytime?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Sure! Just open a ticket.

&lt;b&gt;Can I use my own domain name for IMAP/POP/SMTP?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Sure, but the SSL certificate is signed for *.mxroute.com so your clients will receive a warning message about it when using SSL ports to connect.

&lt;b&gt;Can I customize webmail?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Sure! You can install Roundcube or any other webmail client on your own server and use it to connect to ours over IMAP, POP3, and SMTP.

&lt;b&gt;Why does MX2 point to the same record as MX1?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
This is a long term project. Read here: https://billing.mxroute.com/announcements.php?id=25

&lt;b&gt;Can I forward all of my e-mail to Gmail, Yahoo, AOL, or Hotmail?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
No. There are alternatives that work just fine:&lt;br&gt;
http://email.about.com/od/yahoomailtip1/qt/How_to_Check_Other_Email_Accounts_with_Yahoo_Mail.htm&lt;br&gt;
https://support.google.com/mail/answer/21289?hl=en&lt;br&gt;
http://windows.microsoft.com/en-us/outlook/yahoo-imap

&lt;b&gt;Can you guarantee that my mail won't land in spam folders?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;
No one can guarantee that. The calculation for most services involves domain + content + IP reputation. I can and will handle the third, but I can't fix a bad reputation with your domain or content.
